  ('b29d132c-1fa6-e62c-1a38-239c0cc0c0d9', 'GR', 'Greece', 'Olive Oil — Peloponnesian Cluster', 'Liá Cultivators', '', 'Peloponnese (Messinia)', 'M', NULL, '', 'Liá Premium Koroneiki — Top-30 EVOO World Ranking 2025.', 'L3', '["Single-varietal Koroneiki"]'::jsonb),
  ('2a94df08-79db-0f1d-ac03-47078c6c8b0f', 'GR', 'Greece', 'Olive Oil — Peloponnesian Cluster', 'Karpea / Kalogeris Group / regional Peloponnesian cooperatives', '', 'Multiple Peloponnesian regions', 'M', NULL, '', 'Multiple regional Peloponnesian cooperatives. For Iriska, direct list at Greek Ministry of Rural Development.', 'L3', '["Kalamata PDO", "Olympia PGI", "Lakonia PGI"]'::jsonb),
  ('9f3a50e9-71dd-238a-93a7-88624dc63bfc', 'GR', 'Greece', 'Olive Oil — Other Greek Regions', 'Lesvos / Mytilini PGI cluster', '', 'Lesvos island (North Aegean)', 'M', NULL, '', 'Lesvos island Adramyttiani and Kolovi cultivars (native to island). Multiple regional producers. Mostly boutique tier.', 'L3', '["Lesvos PGI / Mytilini PGI"]'::jsonb),
  ('9a6ea5b4-aa89-f643-093f-f7c214981327', 'GR', 'Greece', 'Olive Oil — Other Greek Regions', 'G-TEAM (Hypereleon brand)', '', 'Arcadian Mountains (Peloponnese)', 'M', NULL, '', 'Hypereleon Ultra Gold, Hypereleon Nutri Arcadian Mountains, Hypereleon Gold — multi-tier premium range. Top-30 EVOO World Ranking 2025.', 'L3', '["Arcadian / Olympia PGI region"]'::jsonb),
  ('c85bae2c-e89b-8ce4-eee0-3aa4e0fa51b3', 'GR', 'Greece', 'Olive Oil — Other Greek Regions', 'Jordan Olivenöl GmbH (German-Greek joint venture)', '', 'Greek sourcing (mostly Peloponnese)', 'M', NULL, '', 'German market specialist for Greek EVOO. Top-20 EVOO World Ranking 2025. "Jordan Olivenöl Natives Bio" and "Bambatsa Nativ Extra" — reliable specialty tier.', 'L3', '["Greek olive oil multi-region"]'::jsonb),
  ('5d055d09-a653-fd6e-ce45-432bf60e8cc5', 'GR', 'Greece', 'Olive Oil — Other Greek Regions', 'Northern Greece (Halkidiki, Thrace) producers', '', 'Northern Greece', 'M', NULL, '', 'Halkidiki olive cluster — also major table-olive zone (see olives section).', 'L3', '["Various Greek northern olive oil PGIs"]'::jsonb),
  ('63f830b0-c10c-ddf0-b45a-cd2ba2abe766', 'GR', 'Greece', 'Table Olives PDO/PGI', 'Kalamata olive cooperatives + Sakellaropoulos / Agrovim (already covered above)', '', 'Messinia (Kalamata) + Lakonia', 'L', NULL, '', '**Kalamon olives** — distinctive almond-shape deep-purple-black olives, traditional brine-cured. Leading global premium table olive (the "Kalamata olive" iconic global brand). Sakellaropoulos and Agrovim already covered above for olive oil; same companies are major Kalamata olive producers.', 'L3', '["Kalamata olive PDO"]'::jsonb),
  ('a576528f-ebd3-3321-1a8d-c1dff5c08c01', 'GR', 'Greece', 'Table Olives PDO/PGI', 'Halkidiki olive producers', '', 'Halkidiki (Northern Greece)', 'L', NULL, '', 'Major green-olive production region. Strong supermarket and tapenade-export positioning. Refer to Greek Olive Producers Association for verified list.', 'L3', '["Konservolia Amfissis PDO", "various Greek PDOs (Halkidiki olives are commercially huge", "mostly green)"]'::jsonb),
  ('2f2af218-0e24-f78d-a5b5-76334ff29bb9', 'GR', 'Greece', 'Table Olives PDO/PGI', 'Throumba Thassou PDO cooperative', '', 'Thassos island (North Aegean)', 'S', NULL, '', 'Niche Thassos sun-cured olives. Premium boutique tier.', 'L3', '["Throumba Thassou PDO (sun-cured wrinkled black olives)"]'::jsonb),
  ('955f6d2c-ed06-858f-8e9b-291dc60d73f8', 'GR', 'Greece', 'Table Olives PDO/PGI', 'Konservolia regional cooperatives (Amfissis, Volou, Stylidas, Artas, Atalantis, Pylias, Rovion)', '', 'Multiple central Greek regions', 'M', NULL, '', 'Multiple regional Konservolia PDO cooperatives — volume-tier mainland Greek table olives. Direct cooperative outreach for verified routing.', 'L3', '["Konservolia (multiple PDOs) — Greek volume green-and-black olives"]'::jsonb),
  ('9b27c3f8-47c0-0003-41ec-acbb7739ee9b', 'GR', 'Greece', 'Mastiha Chiou PDO', 'Chios Mastiha Growers Association (CMGA)', 'Compulsory cooperative (founded 1938 under Greek Law 1390)', 'Chios island (North Aegean)', 'L', TRUE, 'gummastic.gr', '**The legally-mandatory single cooperative for Mastiha Chiou PDO production** — statutory monopoly under Law 1390/1938. **20 primary cooperatives** in 24 Mastiha villages (Mastihohoria) of southern Chios. **~4,500 members; ~1,700 active.** Annual production ~230 tonnes. **2024 turnover: €23 million.** PDO since 1997. UNESCO Intangible Cultural Heritage 2014. EU Medicines Agency-approved as natural plant-origin medicine 2016. Reference unique Greek culinary specialty for HoReCa worldwide.', 'L3', '["Mastiha Chiou PDO (the unique Pistacia lentiscus tree-resin \"tears\")"]'::jsonb),
  ('e509d2c7-677a-c198-3098-b7c7b8eb7fa9', 'GR', 'Greece', 'Mastiha Chiou PDO', 'Mediterra S.A. (CMGA''s commercial arm)', 'Chios Mastiha Growers Association', 'Chios island (commercial division)', 'L', TRUE, 'mastihashop.com', '**The commercial subsidiary of CMGA, founded 2002.** **Mastihashop retail network** — global "Mastiha embassies" stores promoting innovative mastic-based products. Multi-channel distribution: supermarket, delicatessen, pharmacies, health food stores. Reference for Mastiha Chiou PDO commercial routing — direct contact for HoReCa partnership and product range.', 'L3', '["Mastiha Chiou PDO", "downstream products"]'::jsonb),
  ('6671dd33-0d08-ebcb-5a80-1f9a417b9f7e', 'GR', 'Greece', 'Krokos Kozanis PDO (Saffron)', 'Kozani Saffron Producers Cooperative ("Cooperative De Safran")', 'Compulsory cooperative (founded 1971 under Legislative Decree 818/1971)', 'Krokos village (Kozani Prefecture, Western Macedonia)', 'L', TRUE, 'safran.gr / krokoskozanispdo.eu', '**The legally-mandatory single cooperative for Krokos Kozanis PDO** — statutory monopoly under Decree 818/1971. ~1,000 members; ~5,000 people employed in saffron cultivation. ISO 9001 certified since 1997. PDO recognition 1999. Cultivation across 25-40 villages of Kozani Prefecture (West Macedonia). One of EU''s five saffron PDOs (alongside Italian Aquila, San Gimignano, Sardegna; Spanish La Mancha). Reference for Greek saffron HoReCa worldwide.', 'L3', '["Krokos Kozanis PDO (saffron — Crocus sativus stigmas)"]'::jsonb),
  ('564842e6-43d4-8d99-b7a4-0941921f7fbb', 'GR', 'Greece', 'Krokos Kozanis PDO (Saffron)', 'Krocus Kozanis Products S.A.', 'Joint venture: Kozani Saffron Cooperative + KORRES (Greek cosmetics/wellness brand)', 'Kozani Prefecture', 'L', TRUE, 'krocuskozanis.com', 'Founded 2007 as joint venture between the Cooperative and KORRES (premium Greek natural cosmetics brand). Develops innovative saffron-based products. Premium positioning. Useful for Iriska as the value-added downstream brand of the saffron cooperative.', 'L3', '["Krokos Kozanis PDO downstream products"]'::jsonb),
  ('4d39ad56-0990-36ee-426d-3413774abbf6', 'GR', 'Greece', 'Greek Honey PDOs', 'Attiki Pittas (Greek honey major producer)', '', 'Attica (Athens area), national sourcing', 'L', TRUE, 'attiki-pittas.gr', 'Greece''s largest honey producer/packer. Multi-region Greek honey including PDO/PGI varietals. Strong supermarket distribution.', 'L3', '["Multiple Greek thyme/pine honey PGIs"]'::jsonb),
  ('2752f42f-a756-cf0d-9b07-4a6a483803a1', 'GR', 'Greece', 'Greek Honey PDOs', 'Melissa-Kikizas honey arm (cross-reference Terra Creta)', '', 'Greece national', 'L', NULL, '', 'Honey division alongside Terra Creta olive oil under Melissa-Kikizas group.', 'L3', '["Greek honey"]'::jsonb),
  ('218ba5d0-9908-784d-9a29-fa0ed18000c7', 'GR', 'Greece', 'Greek Honey PDOs', 'Mela Elatou Mainalou Vanilia PDO cooperative', '', 'Mainalo Mountains (Peloponnese)', 'S', NULL, '', 'Niche premium Mainalo fir-tree honey PDO. Limited boutique production.', 'L3', '["Mela Elatou Mainalou Vanilia PDO (fir-tree honeydew", "vanilla note)"]'::jsonb),
  ('aa1c08a3-9e5a-79a6-8a6c-7135751ec24c', 'GR', 'Greece', 'Greek Honey PDOs', 'Mela Krokeon PDO (Lakonia)', '', 'Krokees (Lakonia)', 'S', NULL, '', 'Niche Lakonian honey PDO.', 'L3', '["Greek honey PDO"]'::jsonb),
  ('2e66a09b-aeac-fc6d-0e94-57a0d88640d0', 'GR', 'Greece', 'Conservas / Mezedes Preserves', 'Santorini Cooperative Union (Fava Santorinis PDO + Tomataki Santorinis PDO)', 'Cooperative', 'Santorini (Cyclades)', 'M', TRUE, '', '**Reference Santorini-specific PDO cooperative.** Yellow split pea (Lathyrus clymenum) for fava puree — iconic Cycladic mezze. Tomataki — volcanic cherry tomato, intense flavor. Reference for Cycladic specialty HoReCa.', 'L3', '["Fava Santorinis PDO (yellow split pea)", "Tomataki Santorinis PDO (volcanic-soil cherry tomato)"]'::jsonb),
  ('f22d10c8-12bc-19e0-6e73-af496052a80e', 'GR', 'Greece', 'Conservas / Mezedes Preserves', 'Greek conservas / mezedes specialty firms', '', 'Various', 'M', NULL, '', 'Greek tinned dolmades, taramosalata, tzatziki etc. — heritage retail commercial category.', 'L3', '["Multiple Greek heritage products (mostly non-PDO but commercially essential)"]'::jsonb),
  ('e959fbc5-4319-b710-e4f4-09dfc5ead2ab', 'GR', 'Greece', 'Conservas / Mezedes Preserves', 'Olympus Foods / Filippo Berio Greek (multi-product)', '', 'Multiple', 'L', NULL, '', 'Multi-product Greek-origin specialty brands.', 'L3', '["Various"]'::jsonb),
  ('e104a1d3-8d79-3e17-5916-4a3ee4be05a2', 'GR', 'Greece', 'Conservas / Mezedes Preserves', 'Mastelo / Cretan rusks (Karpea)', '', 'Crete', 'M', NULL, '', 'Heritage Cretan dried-bread rusks for dakos preparation. Mostly non-PDO but commercially essential for Cretan menu service.', 'L3', '["Heritage Cretan rusks (paximadia)"]'::jsonb),
  ('a76cec79-88f3-e740-15c1-8c2236ff344d', 'GR', 'Greece', 'Yogurt (heritage, mostly non-PDO)', 'Total (Fage)', 'FAGE Dairy Industry S.A.', 'Athens HQ; Greek + US production', 'L', TRUE, 'fage.eu / fageusa.com', 'Greece''s most-internationally-recognized yogurt brand. Strong global presence (especially US — also produced in US for US market). Heritage Greek yogurt — not PDO-protected (Greek-style yogurt is descriptive, not PDO-registered).', 'L3', '["Greek-style yogurt (heritage", "not PDO)"]'::jsonb),
  ('8c3b7859-42de-35b0-8791-eb8dd02591c7', 'GR', 'Greece', 'Yogurt (heritage, mostly non-PDO)', 'Total / Greek God / Olympus / Kri-Kri yogurt arms', '', 'Various', 'L', NULL, '', 'Multiple Greek dairies produce Greek-style yogurt (volume retail).', 'L3', '[]'::jsonb)
